the political thought and social patterns that characterized this religious stream. Besides questioning the paradigm of the Imamate, we also explore how stateless societies could be regulated by collective social and religious institutions.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn French.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aIbaditesxHistoryyTo 1500vCongresses. 0aIslamxDoctrinesxHistoryvCongresses. 0aIslamic philosophyvCongresses. 4aIbaditen. 4aNordafrika. 4aPolitikgeschichte. 4aSozialgeschichte. 7aRELIGION / Islam / General.2bisacsh  aIbadism.  aNorth Africa.  apolitical history.  asocial history.1 aAillet, Cyrille, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAillet, Cyrille, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aAmara, Allaoua, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBahaz, Ibrahim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrett, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCapel, Chloé, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChekhab-Abudaya, Mounia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDaghfous, Radhi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDonner, Fred M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDridi, Moez, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFili, Abdallah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrancesca, Ersilia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrantsouzoff, Sergueï A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGaiser, Adam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHassen, Mohamed, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.l